title: Independent candidate Malik Tariq Awan wins PK-82 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Malik Tariq Awan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-82, Peshawar-XI by securing 20,334 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Kamran Khan Bangash who bagged 14,030 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 36.67 per cent.
